    <description>Ligny and Wavre 1815 is a complete game in the Jours de Gloire series. It covers the battles which occurred on June 16th, 18th and 19th, during Napol&amp;eacute;on&amp;rsquo;s offensive in Belgium against the armies of Wellington and Bl&amp;uuml;cher.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Ligny 1815 is the last victory of Napoleon:  with his Arm&amp;eacute;e du Nord, the Emperor attacks Bl&amp;uuml;cher&amp;rsquo;s Prussians and inflicts them a severe defeat. But the the bulk of the Prussian army survived and went on to play a pivotal role two days later at Waterloo&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Wavre 1815 shows the two days useless fights of Grouchy corps against Thielmann, when, at the same time, Napoleon was decisivly beated at Waterloo.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;An additionnal scenario features a &amp;laquo; what if Grouchy have been abble to reinforce Napoleon at Waterloo? &amp;raquo;. It requires the Les Quatre-Bras and Waterloo 1815 module to be played.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Ligny, June 16th 1815: Napoleon vs. Bl&amp;uuml;cher&amp;#10;Wavre, June 18th and June 19th 1815: Grouchy vs. Thielmann&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Ligny 1815 and Wavre 1815 are the 42nd and 43rd battles of the Jours de Gloire series.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
